## 3. Scaffold sequence (demo-builder step 0)

```bash
cd upwork-runs/bowling-shirt-designer
npx create-next-app@15.5.20 demo-src \
  --ts --tailwind --app --no-eslint --no-src-dir \
  --import-alias "@/*"
cd demo-src
npm install three @react-three/fiber@8.18.0 @react-three/drei@9.122.0 zustand
npm install -D @types/three
```

Then overwrite `next.config.ts` (or `.js`) with the config above.

---

## 4. ~12-file map (stay under budget — stack functionality per file)

```
demo-src/
  next.config.js
  tailwind.config.ts           -- palette + Bebas Neue / Inter
  app/
    layout.tsx                 -- Google Fonts (Bebas Neue + Inter), global CSS, metadata
    page.tsx                   -- homepage: hero + lazy Canvas section + AuditSection
    globals.css                -- CSS vars, Tailwind @layer base
  components/
    ShirtCustomizer.tsx        -- 'use client'; next/dynamic Canvas wrapper (ssr:false)
    ShirtCanvas.tsx            -- r3f Canvas, OrbitControls, procedural shirt mesh, Decal
    OptionsPanel.tsx           -- color pickers, pattern picker, text-on-back, size/qty, Add-to-Cart
    CartDrawer.tsx             -- slide-over cart, thumbnails from canvas.toDataURL
    AuditSection.tsx           -- Before/After table + Roadmap panel
  lib/
    store.ts                   -- Zustand store (all customizer + cart state)
    patterns.ts                -- 6 canvas-generated CanvasTexture factories
```

Total: 12 files (layout + page + globals + 5 components + 2 lib + config x2).
If the build gets tight, merge CartDrawer into OptionsPanel (save 1 file).

