## 14. API calls from the frontend (OptionsPanel.tsx)

Backend base: `https://api.michaelwegter.com/bowling`

```ts
// Save customization
async function saveSession(state: Partial<ShirtState>) {
  const res = await fetch('https://api.michaelwegter.com/bowling/session', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify(state),
  });
  const { id } = await res.json();
  return id as string;
}

// Load by URL param ?s=<id> on mount
async function loadSession(id: string) {
  const res = await fetch(`https://api.michaelwegter.com/bowling/session/${id}`);
  return res.json();
}
```

Share URL pattern: `window.location.origin + '/demos/bowling-shirt-designer/?s=' + id`
On page load: `const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search); const sid = params.get('s');`

