:root {
  --navy:  #1a1f3c;
  --cream: #f5f0e8;
  --coral: #e84040;
  --gold:  #f5a623;
  --white: #ffffff;
}
body {
  background: var(--navy);
  color: var(--cream);
  font-family: var(--font-inter), system-ui, sans-serif;
}
```

---

## 16. AuditSection sample content

Before/After table rows (render as a styled `<table>`):

| Problem (Client's Clarity Finding) | Root Cause | This Build's Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Dead clicks / "undefined is not a object" | Unguarded nested state reads; missing null checks on async store hydration | Zustand selectors with safe defaults; no unguarded optional chaining |
| Homepage bounce (instant exit after load) | Heavy synchronous JS bundle blocks first paint; canvas lib in critical path | `next/dynamic` + `ssr:false` code-splits the Three.js bundle; homepage is interactive before canvas mounts |
| Unresponsive color swaps | Multiple setState calls triggering cascading re-renders + re-layout | Single Zustand action per interaction; Three.js material `color` prop updated once per frame |

Remediation Roadmap steps (render as numbered checklist):
1. Audit all selector calls for `undefined` — wrap with `?? fallback` or `if (!x) return`.
2. Move Three.js / canvas to a dynamic import with `ssr:false`. Measure LCP before/after.
3. Replace `setState` chains with a single Zustand action that patches multiple fields atomically.
4. Add an `ErrorBoundary` around the Canvas; log to Clarity custom events.
5. Run Clarity "Dead Click" heatmap against the patched build; confirm the hot zones resolve.

